race.comment: PUNIC WAR (4) is an 11-start maiden who finished fourth at his most recent outing over 1500m at Sandown-Hillside. Had a few goes, but racing too well to dismiss and is a nice price, so can play each way. RUMBLE TOWN (6) lifted strongly only to just miss last start over 1300m at Seymour. Perfectly placed and well-drawn, so sure to take plenty of stopping. ANGEL FEET (3) hasn't placed in five starts, but most have been in town in much tougher races than this and is likely to have benefited from the time between preps. THE BETTER HUSBAND (9) finished fourth at both runs last prep, but beat stablemate Equivaster - who is engaged in R1 - in a recent trial so if she runs well earlier it can be considered a good guide.
